Well, that's fucking retarded. Not because of the chances of an attacker getting ahold of the machine seconds after its been shut down and throwing LN2 all over the motherboard, but because Tails is encouraged to be used along another operating system, and the whole point is to be an amnesic system, meaning all data is gone after the computer is turned off. Not so amnesic if Windows 10 can slurp up all your sikrit data after a reboot now isn't it?
